==English==

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ætɪk|-ætɪk]]

===Adjective===
'''adiabatic'''
#{{physics}} [[Concern]]ing a [[reversible]] [[thermodynamic]] [[process]] that [[occur]]s without [[gain]] or [[loss]] of [[heat]].
#[[Meteorology]] A [[thermodynamic]] [[change]] of [[state]] of a [[system]] in which there is no transfer of [[heat]] or [[mass]] across the boundaries of the system. In an adiabatic process, [[compression]] always results in warming, [[expansion]] in cooling. In Meteorology the adiabatic process often is also taken to be a reversible process. For many purposes, changes of state in the free atmosphere over periods of two days or less are assumed to be adiabatic. 

